    Scope and Contents
WWII CONSCIENTIOUS OBJECTORS PROJECT 
Houser, conscientious objector during WWII, discusses pacifism, his decision to resist the draft, performing alternate service during the war, racial issues, teaching experiences at an African American school in Mississippi, race relations, social issues and revolutions. 1 tape, 90 mins., 29 pp. 
Interview by C. Arthur Bradley, 1988 
